Miscellaneous Highlights: Cleveland Guardians (92-67) Clinched division title. Trail the Yankees by a half-game for the best record in the AL.
Houston Astros (86-73) Clinched division title and locked into the No. 3 seed in the AL playoffs.
Los Angeles Dodgers (94-64) Clinched playoff berth. Lead the Padres by three games in the division after defeating San Diego 4-3 on Wednesday in the middle game of a three-game home series.
Philadelphia Phillies (94-65) Clinched the division title. Clinched a first-round bye on Wednesday after beating the visiting Chicago Cubs 9-6 on Wednesday in the finale of a three-game series.
Milwaukee Brewers (90-68) Clinched division title. Locked into the No. 3 NL seed after losing 2-1 to the host Pittsburgh Pirates on Wednesday in the middle game of a three-game series.
New York Yankees (92-66) Clinched a playoff spot. Can clinch No. 1 seed and wild-card-round bye with a win over the visiting Orioles in the finale of a three-game series on Thursday.
Baltimore Orioles (88-70) Clinched a playoff spot. Four games behind New York in the division after beating the Yankees 9-7 on Wednesday, with both teams having four games to play.
